OL,3,CArgentina risk Fifa action for
OL,4,Cdisplaying Falklands banner after semi-
OL,5,Cfinal win
OL,7,FArgentina players celebrated their
OL,8,FWorld Cup semi-final victory over
OL,9,FEngland by holding a banner about the
OL,10,FFalkland Islands on the pitch in
OL,11,FAtlanta, flouting Fifa rules.
OL,13,FThe world football's governing body
OL,14,Fbans political gestures.
OL,16,FIts code of conduct prohibits
OL,17,F"banners, flags, flyers, apparel and
OL,18,Fother paraphernalia that are of a
OL,19,Fpolitical, offensive, and/or
OL,20,Fdiscriminatory nature" inside stadiums.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
